<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">I know, right? This is really easy to miss because of the way the author chose to downplay it in the book. Which is really a shame! <br/><br/>Before Brisbane se<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">I know, right? This is really easy to miss because of the way the author chose to downplay it in the book. Which is really a shame! <br /><br />Before Brisbane sends her away in the carriage at the Gypsy camp, he traps her against a tree. <br />------------<br /> "Brisbane, say something. If you wish to strike me, do it and get it over with. I know you are frightfully angry, and you have every right..."<br /> I stopped then because he made me. He did not strike me; instead he did something I had never expected. He reached for me. It was sometime before he let me go.<br /> When he did, I was breathing far too fast and I tasted blood on my lips.<br />------------<br />If you blinked, you missed it.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
